Steps to install and set up SASS
Create the project directory

In my alx-intermediate-frontend repository, let me run:
mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
cd 0x03-sass_scss

(Optional) Install Node Version 20.16 using NVM

If Node isnâ€™t already installed, install NVM and Node 20.16:
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
exit

Reopen your terminal, then run:
nvm install 20.16
nvm use 20.16

Verify installation:
node -v
npm -v

Install SASS

Once Node is installed, run:
npm install sass -v 3.7.4

Verify that SASS is installed:
npx sass --version

Create your installation script file

In the 0x03-sass_scss directory, create an empty file named:
touch 0-installation-script

Open the file and write the steps you followed.
Example content for 0-installation-script 
# Steps to install SASS

1. Created the directory 0x03-sass_scss inside alx-intermediate-frontend repository.
2. Installed NVM:
   $ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
3. Exited the terminal and reopened it.
4. Installed Node version 20.16:
   $ nvm install 20.16
   $ nvm use 20.16
5. Verified Node and NPM installation:
   $ node -v
   $ npm -v
6. Installed SASS version 3.7.4:
   $ npm install sass -v 3.7.4
7. Verified SASS installation:
   $ npx sass --version


